      "updated_at": "2016-12-05T07:59:36Z",
      "body": "Agree. Split js framework into small parts would be very convenient for developers.\r\n\r\nCurrently we already have:\r\n\r\n+ [weex-js-framework](https://www.npmjs.com/package/weex-js-framework): The js framework of Weex.\r\n+ [weex-js-runtime](https://www.npmjs.com/package/weex-js-runtime) The runtime of Weex, which is shared with all \"cores\".\r\n+ [weex-vue-framework](https://www.npmjs.com/package/weex-vue-framework): The Vue ^2.0 \"core\" of Weex. (The source code is in the [Vue repo](https://github.com/vuejs/vue).)\r\n+ [weex-html5](https://www.npmjs.com/package/weex-html5): Weex HTML5 renderer.\r\n+ [weex-components](https://www.npmjs.com/package/weex-components): A group of simple and useful weex components.\r\n\r\nBut they may not be suitable for use alone, some of them is hard to use (`weex-js-framework` contains ES6 modules, which couldn't running on node platform recently). \r\n\r\nI will continue decoupling the internal modules of Weex and publish more packages."
    }
