  "closed_at": "2016-11-28T15:55:06Z",
  "body": "## What the situation is now\r\nif someone want to use another framework as WEEX  js framework, he will want to modify the source code and run build:native again\r\n## What to expect \r\nSeparating the  js framework core part, and developers can use npm install it, and using another framework can be  something  easy as the codes shown below\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport Core from 'weex-core';\r\nimport FW from './myframework';\r\nimport BuiltIn from './myBuiltIn';\r\n\r\nCore.addFrameWork(FW);\r\nCore.addBuiltIn(BuiltIn);\r\nmodule.exports Core;\r\n``` \r\n\r\n## why doing this\r\nWEEX js framework is changing all the time, including it building tool and  framework it used, custom framework's developing jsfm and building tools are not the same, and building them together  cause some problems. \r\n"
}
